{"lemma":"شاذٌّ","slug":"شاذٌّ","root":"ش.ذ.ذ","root_slug":"ش-ذ-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ذ-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21970"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B0%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"isolated, separate, detached, alone"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"irregular, anomalous, atypical, abnormal, unusual, aberrant, eccentric, extraordinary, singular, offbeat, curious, odd, peculiar, strange, weird","examples":[{"text":"أَفْعَالٌ مُطَّرِدَةٌ وَشَاذَّةٌ","english":"regular and irregular verbs"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noncanonical"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"homosexual","tags":["euphemistic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb شَذَّ (šaḏḏa, “to be separated, be irregular”)."},"ipa":["/ʃaːðð/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21970","headword_ar":"شَاذٌّ","root":"$*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becomes, apart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that falls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comes, out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth, from the generality of things, general assemblage, main body, bulk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common mass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which it pertains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apart from his companions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, L:) and [app. a beast]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taking fright, and running away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aAnN","text_ar":"شُذَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. thereof, like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ub~aAnN","text_ar":"شُبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAb~N","text_ar":"شَابٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aA*N","text_ar":"شُذَّاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with analogy;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*~aAn","text_ar":"شَذَّان","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in a similar sense, but is an epithet of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEolaAn","text_ar":"فِعْلَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", not a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA*~N","text_ar":"شَاذٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yadaEu fulaAnN $aA*~FA walaA","text_ar":"مَا يَدَعُ فُلَانٌ شَاذًّا وَلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAd~FA A_il~aA qatalahu","text_ar":"نَادًّا اـِلَّا قَتَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one does not leave any one apart from his companions, nor any one taking fright and running away, but he slays him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said of a courageous man whom no one encounters without his slaying him. (IAar, L.) And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aAnu qawomK","text_ar":"شُذَّانُ قَوْمٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those, of a people, who have become apart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate, from their companions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aA*u Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"شُذَّاذُ النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those who are among a people but do not belong to their tribes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor to their places of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who are scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, of people;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*~aAnu","text_ar":"شَذَّانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aAnuhumo","text_ar":"شُذَّانُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN $u*~aA*N","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ شُذَّاذٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A people not among their own tribe nor in their own places of abode:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people among another people, not among their own tribes nor in their own places of abode."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aA*u AlA=faAqi","text_ar":"شُذَّاذُ الا=فَاقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The strangers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 352.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA $u*~aA*FA","text_ar":"جَاوُوا شُذَّاذًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came few in number."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibili","text_ar":"الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*~aAnu","text_ar":"شَذَّانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aAnuhaA","text_ar":"شُذَّانُهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Those that are scattered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, of the camels."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aAnu AlHaSaY","text_ar":"شُذَّانُ الحَصَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaSaY","text_ar":"الحَصَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*~aAnu","text_ar":"شَذَّانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, IJ, M, L, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What are scatterred,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, of pebbles;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what have flown about, and become scattered"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispersed, thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) and in like manner one says of other things, (L, K,) or of similar things. (M, L.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a word, form or measure, construction, or government, it signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deviating from the common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant, course of speech in respect of analogy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rule; deviating from common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant, analogy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rule; extraordinary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceptional, as to rule;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anomalous, abnormal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"irregular:"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a word, &c., though itself admitted if agreeable with common usage, is not taken as an example to be imitated: also, applied to the same,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deviating from the common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant, course of speech in respect of usage; deviating from common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constant, usage; extraordinary,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceptional, as to usage; unusual:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[used absolutely to express each of these significations; the context in general showing clearly which signification is meant: the former is that which is most frequently intended:] a word, &c., may be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$A*~","text_ar":"شاذّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of usage but agreeable with common analogy or rule; as the pret. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya*aru","text_ar":"يَذَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadaEu","text_ar":"يَدَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the regular phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makaAnN muboqilN","text_ar":"مَكَانٌ مُبْقِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the epithet more commonly heard being"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqilN","text_ar":"بَاقِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$A*~","text_ar":"شاذّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of analogy, or rule, but agreeable with common usage; as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axowaSa","text_ar":"اَخْوَصَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~imovu","text_ar":"الرِّمْثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotaSowabotu AlA^amora","text_ar":"اِسْتَصْوَبْتُ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$A*~","text_ar":"شاذّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of analogy, or rule, and of usage, together; as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSowuwnN","text_ar":"مَصْوُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misokN madowuwfN","text_ar":"مِسْكٌ مَدْوُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mz, 12th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":": [and the like is said, but less fully, in the Msb:]) the pl. masc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$u*~aA*N","text_ar":"شُذَّاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaA*~u","text_ar":"شَوَاذُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mz, ib.) See 4, last sentence. [See also the contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~aridN","text_ar":"مُطَّرِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$a*~a","text_ar":"شَذَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter part.] ―         -b3-  Applied to a tradition, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having a single ascription, attested by a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"single"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheykh, whether he be trustworthy or not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the latter case, not accepted: in the former case, one hesitates respecting it, and does not adduce it as an argument, or evidence. (KT.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","Lth","M","IJ","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B0/","headword_ar":"شاذ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23329#a6041b","body_html":"<span>الشاذ: ما يكون مخالفًا للقياس، من غير نظر إلى قلة وجوده وكثرته.<br></span><br>الشاذ من الحديث: هو الذي له إسناد واحد يشهد بذلك شيخ؛ ثقة كان أو غير ثقة، فما كان من غير ثقة، فمتروك لا يقبل، وما كان عن ثقة يتوقف فيه ولا يحتج به.<br><br>الشاذ: وهو على نوعين شاذ مقبول، وشاذ مردود؛ أما الشاذ المقبول؛ فهو الذي يجيء على خلاف القياس، ويقبل عند الفصحاء، والبلغاء، وأما الشاذ المردود؛ فهو الذي يجيء على خلاف القياس، ولا يقبل عند الفصحاء، والبلغاء؛ والفرق بين الشاذ، والنادر، والضعيف، هو: أن الشاذ يكون في كلام العرب كثيرًا لكن بخلاف القياس، والنادر هو الذي يكون وجوده قليلًا لكن يكون على القياس، والضعيف هو الذي لم يصل حكمه إلى الثبوت."}]}}